{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d6d784e-ddd6-4eb3-9ffa-ebc7237f68ce","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** For xUnit `[Theory]` tests, use `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` — the `Skip` property is on the test attribute itself, not a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e0fb30cf-c9c3-4ce1-b71c-7d5c8359c4ea","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":308,"requestId":"E3D1:321F09:56D89A:63F226:6A052398"},"id":"e03646a3-41a4-48dc-9f52-0df21c612fb9","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:21:35.061Z","parentId":"1c326666-e9b1-42cd-90c6-84a684bc30b8"}
